---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/PageHeader.astro';
import TerminalHero from '../components/TerminalHero.astro';
import '../styles/prose.css';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About xtinyrabbit">
  <div class="container">
    <PageHeader title="About" />
    <TerminalHero />
    <article class="about-article prose">
      <p>
        I'm a software engineer. I started in QA, moved through consulting, settled
        into backend systems, and now spend most of my time at the intersection of
        AI tooling, developer experience, and the harness work that makes all of it
        actually run. The throughline is the same: get the system to tell you when
        something is wrong, preferably before users do.
      </p>

      <p>
        Most of my work lives in distributed systems — Go services talking over
        gRPC and Kafka, REST APIs that need to stay honest under load, GraphQL
        layers that shouldn't become a mess. CI/CD, observability, the full
        DevOps loop. I lean toward TDD not as dogma but because fast feedback
        loops make the work easier to trust.
      </p>

      <p>
        I care about simplicity. Not as an aesthetic — as a strategy. Complex
        systems fail in complex ways; simple ones fail in ways you can reason
        about. The best system design decisions I've made were subtractions.
        The worst were additions I thought I'd need later.
      </p>

      <p>
        This blog is where I write about things I've figured out, usually the
        hard way. Distributed systems, tooling, the design decisions that look
        obvious in hindsight. Fail fast, learn fast, write it down.
      </p>

      <h2>What I work with</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Go — primary language for backend and systems work</li>
        <li>Distributed systems: REST, gRPC, GraphQL, Kafka</li>
        <li>DevOps, CI/CD, developer experience tooling</li>
        <li>AI integrations and agent harness infrastructure</li>
        <li>Fullstack when the problem calls for it</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Find me elsewhere</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/xlargerabbit" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a></li>
        <li><a href="/rss.xml">RSS feed</a></li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .container { padding-block: 3rem 5rem; }
  .about-article { max-width: var(--prose-width); }
</style>
